From 43ccb9817e6ec1c8ca1eb2bd11471a984e64f94b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 03:17:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.2g: Migrate 2 public member pages to useQuery
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Sixth and FINAL slice of the T2.2 react-query fan-out. Migrates the
two remaining user-facing pages with read-side entity fetches:
PartnersPage (public) and SupportTickets (member).

Files (2):
- src/pages/PartnersPage.jsx  (+10/-7)
  Single useQuery for Partner.filter({ is_active: true }). Simplest
  case — no mutations, no dependent queries, no cache invalidation.

- src/pages/SupportTickets.jsx  (+13/-16)
  useQuery for SupportTicket.filter({ reported_by_user_id: user.id })
  gated by 'enabled: !!user?.id'. Both handleSubmit (new ticket) and
  handleComment (add reply) call refreshTickets() instead of load().

This completes the T2.2 fan-out. Pages intentionally NOT migrated:

- Messages.jsx and ServiceRequests.jsx — deferred to T2.4
  (god-component decomposition). Their fetch logic is tangled with
  the subscription lifecycle and will be cleanly separated when
  those pages are broken into focused components.

- Onboarding.jsx — state-machine page, not a reactive-data page.
  Its imperative write-then-read flow fights useQuery's declarative
  model. Uses useRefetchCurrentUser from T2.1, which is the right
  tool for its pattern. No change warranted.

Final T2.2 tally: 17 of ~18 page files migrated to useQuery across
six PRs (T2.2a/b/d/e/f/g). The remaining 2 (Messages, ServiceRequests)
fold into T2.4.

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
- Scoped lint: 0 errors, 1 pre-existing warning
- npm run build: succeeds
- All useEffect/useCallback/load() removed from PartnersPage and
  SupportTickets (member)
